What?
----

APP: abc.war

Dependency: JDK/JRE, Tomcat

Installed it using Ansible playbook >>> on the server


==> If we wanted to deploy two apps with  conflicting dependencies

    APP1 --> JDK14
    APP2 --> JDK11

==> We can create container for each app with each container has its own version of software
==> Containers are seperate with each other. one can't access another

==> Containers doesn't have their own OS. They share a common OS which is system OS.

==> Container is virtualization at application level ==> APP environment ==> Uses file system
==> Virtual Machine is virtualization at machine level

==> Container is a process while Image is a sitting binary information with which container is created

==> Containers can share their data using host machine common file location